1 Now one carries us of the hard banks;
2 and the smoke of the stream from above shadows,
3 so that from the fire it saves the water and the banks.

4 As Flemings between Guizzante and Bruges, 5 fearing the flood that rushes towards them, 6 make the shield so that the sea flees;
7 and as Paduans along the Brenta, 8 to defend their villas and their castles, 9 before Carentana feels the heat:
10 to such an image those were made, 11 although neither so high nor so thick, 12 whatever they were, the master made them.

34 I said to him: “As much as I can, I come gladly;
35 and if you wish that you settle with me,
36 I will do it, if it pleases to this one who goes with me.”

40 Therefore go onward: I will come to you in rags;
41 and then I will rejoin my band,
42 that goes weeping its eternal damages.

